name: Easy Chicken and Dumplings
author: Jen
summary: A super easy way to make chicken and dumplings. My husband and kids loved it.
ingredients: 4  skinless, boneless chicken breast halves, cubed, or more as needed
salt and ground black pepper to taste
2 ¼ cups baking mix (such as Bisquick ®)
directions: Combine chicken broth, chicken breast cubes, onion, carrots, celery, bay leaf, salt, and pepper in a large pot; bring to a boil
Reduce heat, cover pot, and simmer until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes
Mix baking mix and milk in a bowl until dough is sticky; drop golf ball-sized pieces of dough into the soup
Cover pot and cook until dumplings are cooked through, about 10 minutes
